      <h1 class="docs-main-title">Boing Network Documentation</h1>
      <p class="docs-lead">Everything you need to know about Boing Network in one place. Use the table of contents to jump to any section — no endless scrolling.</p>

      <section id="overview" class="doc-section">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>Boing Network is an authentic L1 blockchain built from first principles: <strong>Security</strong> → <strong>Scalability</strong> → <strong>Decentralization</strong> → <strong>Authenticity</strong> → <strong>Transparency</strong>. It is independent of other chains and designed for sustainable value, uncapped supply with floor-triggered rebalancing, and 100% transparent governance and tokenomics.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="getting-started" class="doc-section">
        <h2>Getting Started</h2>
        <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Rust</strong> — Latest stable (1.70+). Use <code>rustup</code>.</li>
          <li><strong>OS</strong> — Linux, macOS, or Windows (WSL recommended on Windows).</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Build</h3>
        <pre><code>cargo build --release</code></pre>
        <h3>Run a Node</h3>
        <p><strong>Full node (non-validator):</strong></p>
        <pre><code>cargo run -p boing-node</code></pre>
        <p>RPC is available at <code>http://127.0.0.1:8545</code> by default.</p>
        <p><strong>Validator node:</strong></p>
        <pre><code>cargo run -p boing-node -- --validator --rpc-port 8545</code></pre>
        <h3>Options</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><code>--validator</code> — Run as a block producer.</li>
          <li><code>--rpc-port &lt;port&gt;</code> — RPC port (default: 8545).</li>
          <li><code>--data-dir &lt;path&gt;</code> — Data directory for chain and state.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>First Transaction</h3>
        <p>Use the JSON-RPC API at <code>http://&lt;host&gt;:8545/</code>. See the <a href="#rpc-api">RPC API</a> section for methods such as <code>boing_submitTransaction</code> and <code>boing_chainHeight</code>.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="network-overview" class="doc-section">
        <h2>Network Overview</h2>
        <p>Boing is a greenfield L1 with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Authentic</strong> — Original architecture, not a fork.</li>
          <li><strong>Independent</strong> — No reliance on other chains.</li>
          <li><strong>Decentralized</strong> — Permissionless validators and nodes.</li>
          <li><strong>Transparent</strong> — 100% openness in design, tokenomics, and governance.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Block time:</strong> ~2 seconds (target).</p>
      </section>

      <section id="tokenomics" class="doc-section">
        <h2>Tokenomics</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Total supply:</strong> Uncapped. New waves are minted when circulating supply reaches a defined floor to rebalance.</li>
          <li><strong>Initial supply:</strong> Set at mainnet launch (fixed amount).</li>
          <li><strong>Fee allocation:</strong> 80% validators, 20% treasury. No required burn.</li>
          <li><strong>Initial supply allocation:</strong> Staking rewards 55%, Treasury 30%, Community & grants 15%. Staking is topped up by waves when the floor is reached.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>All parameters (floor, wave size, fee split) are on-chain and transparent. See the <a href="/#tokenomics">landing page tokenomics</a> for charts.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="architecture" class="doc-section">
        <h2>Architecture & Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Native Account Abstraction</strong> — Gasless txs, social recovery, session keys as protocol primitives.</li>
          <li><strong>Adaptive Gas Model</strong> — Gas adapts to congestion with predictable caps.</li>
          <li><strong>Native Cross-Chain Primitives</strong> — Protocol-level bridges and messaging.</li>
          <li><strong>Transparent Slashing</strong> — Auditable slashing conditions and appeal mechanisms.</li>
          <li><strong>On-Chain Governance</strong> — Time-locked parameter changes (proposal → cooling → execution).</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="rpc-api" class="doc-section">
        <h2>RPC API</h2>
        <p>Boing nodes expose a JSON-RPC 2.0 HTTP interface. <strong>Base URL:</strong> <code>http://&lt;host&gt;:8545/</code> (default port 8545).</p>
        <h3>Request format</h3>
        <pre><code>{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"method":"boing_chainHeight","params":[]}</code></pre>
        <h3>Methods</h3>
        <dl class="rpc-methods">
          <dt><code>boing_submitTransaction</code></dt>
          <dd>Params: <code>[hex_signed_tx]</code>. Submit a signed transaction.</dd>
          <dt><code>boing_chainHeight</code></dt>
          <dd>Params: <code>[]</code>. Current chain height (u64).</dd>
          <dt><code>boing_getBlockByHeight</code></dt>
          <dd>Params: <code>[height]</code>. Block by height (u64).</dd>
          <dt><code>boing_getBlockByHash</code></dt>
          <dd>Params: <code>[hex_block_hash]</code>. Block by 32-byte hash (hex).</dd>
          <dt><code>boing_getAccountProof</code></dt>
          <dd>Params: <code>[hex_account_id]</code>. Merkle proof for account.</dd>
          <dt><code>boing_verifyAccountProof</code></dt>
          <dd>Params: <code>[hex_proof, hex_state_root]</code>. Verify Merkle proof.</dd>
          <dt><code>boing_simulateTransaction</code></dt>
          <dd>Params: <code>[hex_signed_tx]</code>. Simulate tx (gas, success).</dd>
          <dt><code>boing_registerDappMetrics</code></dt>
          <dd>Params: <code>[hex_contract, hex_owner]</code>. Register dApp for incentives.</dd>
          <dt><code>boing_submitIntent</code></dt>
          <dd>Params: <code>[hex_signed_intent]</code>. Submit signed intent for solver.</dd>
        </dl>
        <h3>Error codes</h3>
        <table class="doc-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Code</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>-32600</td><td>Invalid Request</td></tr>
            <tr><td>-32601</td><td>Method not found</td></tr>
            <tr><td>-32602</td><td>Invalid params</td></tr>
            <tr><td>-32000</td><td>Server error</td></tr>
            <tr><td>-32016</td><td>Rate limit exceeded</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <section id="operations" class="doc-section">
        <h2>Operations</h2>
        <h3>CLI</h3>
        <table class="doc-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Command</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><code>boing init [name]</code></td><td>Scaffold a new dApp project</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>boing dev [--port 8545]</code></td><td>Start local dev chain</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>boing deploy [path]</code></td><td>Deploy contract or config</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>boing metrics register --contract &lt;hex&gt; --owner &lt;hex&gt;</code></td><td>Register contract for dApp incentives</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>boing completions &lt;shell&gt;</code></td><td>Shell completions (bash, zsh, fish, etc.)</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <h3>Monitoring</h3>
        <p>Chain height via RPC:</p>
        <pre><code>curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8545/ -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"method":"boing_chainHeight","params":[]}'</code></pre>
        <p>Set <code>RUST_LOG=info</code> (or <code>debug</code> / <code>trace</code>) before running the node for logs.</p>
        <h3>Troubleshooting</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Node won't start</strong> — Ensure RPC port is free; check <code>RUST_LOG=debug</code>; on Windows try WSL if needed.</li>
          <li><strong>Transaction not included</strong> — Enable validator mode for block production; use <code>boing_simulateTransaction</code> first.</li>
          <li><strong>Method not found</strong> — Use exact method name (case-sensitive); params must be a JSON array.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="security" class="doc-section">
        <h2>Security</h2>
        <p>RPC endpoints are rate-limited per configuration. For security incidents:</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Detect</strong> — Monitor logs and community reports.</li>
          <li><strong>Assess</strong> — Classify severity (Low / Medium / High / Critical).</li>
          <li><strong>Contain</strong> — Isolate affected systems.</li>
          <li><strong>Communicate</strong> — Notify validators and users as appropriate.</li>
          <li><strong>Remediate</strong> — Apply fixes; coordinate upgrades via governance if needed.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>Audit reports and bug bounty details are published transparently. See the repository for current security standards.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="governance" class="doc-section">
        <h2>Governance & Transparency</h2>
        <p>Boing commits to <strong>100% transparency</strong>:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Protocol design</strong> — Open specs and auditable code.</li>
          <li><strong>Tokenomics</strong> — Emission, fee split, and wave parameters on-chain and documented.</li>
          <li><strong>Governance</strong> — On-chain proposals, votes, and outcomes.</li>
          <li><strong>Validator & staking</strong> — Clear slashing conditions and reward distribution.</li>
          <li><strong>Treasury</strong> — Public accounts and governance-approved disbursements.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Trust is earned through verification, not promises. All parameters are verifiable on-chain.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="resources" class="doc-section">
        <h2>Resources</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/">Landing page</a> — Tokenomics, roadmap, ecosystem.</li>
          <li><a href="/developers/quickstart">Developer quickstart</a> — CLI, SDK, local dev.</li>
          <li><a href="/network/status">Network status</a> — When available.</li>
          <li><a href="/about">About</a> — Design philosophy and pillars.</li>
          <li><a href="/community">Community</a> — GitHub, governance, grants.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Full design plan, RPC spec, runbook, and security standards are in the <a href="https://github.com/chiku524/boing-network" target="_blank" rel="noopener">boing-network</a> repository.</p>
      </section>
